In a press conference, President Biden announced that the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine has received full approval from the FDA. He urged Americans who have been waiting for full approval to go get vaccinated now. The President emphasized that the vaccine is safe, effective, and free. He also addressed concerns about the Delta variant, stating that cases are still rising, especially among the unvaccinated. He urged parents to ensure that everyone around their children who can be vaccinated is vaccinated and to have their children wear masks when leaving home. The President highlighted the progress made in the vaccination effort, with overall weekly new vaccinations up more than 56 percent from a month ago. He also called on more companies in the private sector to require vaccinations for their employees. The President concluded by urging Americans to get vaccinated for the sake of themselves, their loved ones, their neighbors, and the country.